Activity: A26 – Research and implement a system bug

Objective
The goal of this activity was to understand how system bugs can affect software behaviour and security.

Method
I researched a simple system bug related to software input handling. I demonstrated this by creating a basic example where incorrect input (such as unexpected characters or invalid values) caused errors or unexpected behaviour in a system.

Findings
- Systems can behave unexpectedly when given invalid or unvalidated input.
- Bugs can lead to crashes or incorrect outputs.
- Proper input validation is important to prevent such issues.

Security Principle
This activity relates to integrity and availability, as bugs can cause incorrect system behaviour or system failures.

Evidence
- photo in evidence folder

Reflection
This activity helped me understand how small bugs can impact system reliability and security. It reinforced the importance of proper input validation.
